These lasers are among the best I have used Theyre nothing like those cheap flea market button cell lasers Oh dont shine them in anyones eyes especially the blue one I felt heat coming off that one The green one is the brightest of the and great for pointing at stars on a clear night Instead of using your finger which is not very accurate the green one can point accurately at a star so people around you can see what youre looking at The blue one is more of a blacklight laser It shines very brightly when hitting white material I measured the core temperature of the blue one which was around degrees Fahrenheit inside the diode The red laser is much brighter than even the dollar ones at OfficeMax All these lasers dont suffer from the dreaded dieout effect I get a constant steady power stream from start to finish Although the product says it doesnt come with AAA batteries It does just two however These batteries are offbrand they died out quickly but for batteries that I wasnt supposed to get they were pretty good Build quality is superb The body is a black soft touch paint and everything else is a nice strong metal Overall a very nice product and great deal

MY POOR RATING HERE IS NOT FOR HP INK CARTRIDGES BUT RATHER FOR MY PURCHASE OF THE HPXL CARTRIDGE THROUGH ASHBY STORE AND FULFILLED BY AMAZONI am one of Amazons biggest fans I believe they generally have the best prices and service around As a result I buy just about everything I possibly can through Amazoncom However this was definitely the WORST purchase I have ever had through AmazonThis seller Ashby Store is quite clearly one of the very worst The Hewlett Packard HPXL tricolor ink cartridge I bought from them fulfilled by Amazon was absolute JUNK To begin with the Amazon packaging box was in perfect condition but the HP box was very beat up and looked old On top of that the HP box was clearly intended to be sold only in a Spanishspeaking country as it was primarily in Spanish listed HP as the Exportador and listed three different Argentinian Brazilian and Mexican companies for which it was ImportadoThe area of the HP box that states the Warranty End Date had that end date carefully and suspiciously covered by a professionallooking sticker identifying the cartridge and stating it was new The HP box which looked as though it might have been previously opened and then resealed contained the usual inner white thin cardboard enclosure that holds the cartridge and that white enclosure also looked as though it might have been previously opened Once I took the cartridge completely out of all packaging the sticker that usually covers the inkjet outlets had ink that had leaked onto it Further the warranty end date printed on the cartridge itself was which translates to March and means the cartridge I received on was more than ten months beyond its warranty expiration date while still being sold at a retail priceJust to be sure of my suspicions I went ahead and installed the cartridge in my printer and then attempted to do the usual printer alignment The page that was printed barely had a mark on it and the printer was telling me to try to do another alignment page Instead I tried the printers clean cartridge maintenance function but again got very poor results with only about of the usual coverage That was enough for meI was desperate to replace the old empty HPXL cartridge that was in my printer so I got a Staples coupon for off and paid for it even less than what I paid through Amazon After installing that new HPXL cartridge from Staples my printer worked perfectlyThe only positive THING I can relate about this experience was Amazons excellent customer service I called them and was immediately issued a refund along with having them set up a free pickup of the WORTHLESS junk cartridge by UPSIF I COULD RATE ASHBY STORE AND THIS PURCHASE WITH FIVE NEGATIVE STARS I WOULD DO SO BUT THATS NOT POSSIBLE THE WORST THEY CAN RECEIVE IT ONE STAR SO THATS WHAT THEY GOT

I have an older version of this printer The good It does all the AIO functions fairly well when working The major physical problem is a poorly designed feeder that clogs easily and is difficult to clear properly The horrible Really bad software Dishonest ink usage figures that shut down the printer instantaneously way before the ink is low So even if you check the ink level you cannot predict when it will run out One major problem is the software It frequently causes malfunctions Sometimes this can be resolved by downloading new drivers Other times it takes literally days working with tech support Beyond that the rigging of the printer to report low ink levels is dishonest and frankly fraudulent From posts on the net it seems that the ink refills timeout and after a date will give a lo ink reading even if the ink is not depleted This is important because of the very high cost of the cartridges The ink supply becomes low and the AIO shuts down totally even if it only tells you one ink is low So if it thinks you are low on cyan you cannot even print in black and white It seems there is no override on these machines What a shame I have an HP Laserjet that had a similar problem how to override the automatic shutdown months ago and I still have no decrease in print quality So regardless of the reason this happens this is dishonest In my case I rarely use my AIO for printing and even more rarely for color printing Last weekend I wanted to make my first I think color copy except for test pages and was told the yellow was low I replaced it Then I was told all the other inks were low So I replaced them No go I suspect that the dates on the cartidges are old I always like to have extras and these have been around for a year So it is pretty obvious to me that something is fishy and comments from others on the web would back up this train ofthought And dont think I have had it out for HP I have used their products and been extremely happy for years I know members of the Packard family Sadly their great products and support are now just a memory Im not sure any of the other manufacturers today are any better Havent tried them but will soon Dr N

For the money this is the best phone system I can think of for home or small business use The base unit has a speakerphone which makes it two phones in one as it has the ability to intercom between the base unit and the handheld Then we bought a so we have a point intercom system As we live in an older home the intercom and the ability to place a phone where we wanted without running phone cords was important to us and I spend a lot less time screaming around the house to call the family members We will purchase two more s in the future to intercom easily throughout the house The s run off the base unit and dont need a phone line which is fantastic not to have to pay the phone company to run lines where we want the phones Also the VTech handsets each have Caller ID which is a very handy feature they show when another handset is in use in case you dont have callwaiting at least you know when someone is excessively tying up the hone line and the speakerphone on each handset is perhaps my favorite feature We have eliminated all the corded phones in the house in favor of this system which has clear connections even outdoors and two houses away from us I can send the kids to the neighbors and can page them from the via the intercom when they need to come home Best of all the original handset we bought flew off the hot tub in a sudden windstorm the battery and battery cover landed in the pool managed to catch the phone itself and after the battery dried it still worked A minor ding on the antenna did not affect how the unit performed We are all pleased with the features of this phone

So let me first start off with the only good note on this printer like the other reviews it is extremely easy to setup the wireless printing feature on this printer and the printer itself prints nicely even in draft mode HOWEVER this printer is a complete disaster from a user perspective Unless you have an endless money supply and dont mind stock piling plenty of replacement cartridgesThis printer is the last straw for me in purchasing HP Inkjet Printer products This printers design clearly shows the number one motivation of HP revenue over customer satisfactionThere are two completely unacceptable functional designs in this printer Each time you install a new inkjet cartridge the printer goes through a printer initializing process During this process the program sucks of the remaining ink cartridges installed So if you replace each of the four cartridges over a one week period without printing a single page each of the remaining cartridges will contain less ink once the last cartridge is installed This means that you basically have to replace all cartridges at the same time unless you dont mind wasting of your ink The MOST FRUSTRATING PART OF THIS PRINTER is the fact that you CANNOT PRINT unless all cartridges are fullSo I am getting ready for a critical meeting in hour I need to print a multimillion dollar proposal for my top client for this meeting I know I have plenty of black ink because I installed a new cartridge yesterday I go to print this important document and the printer WILL NOT PRINT MY BLACK AND WHITE DOCUMENT BECAUSE THE CYAN INK was now out of ink Now I know for a fact that this Cyan printer cartridge contained at least ink when I installed the new black ink cartridge because a ran the printer report So now I am panicking and grab another Cyan ink cartridge that I know contained of ink remaining when I replaced it It once again goes through it printer initializing process and now it wont print my BLACK AND WHITE DOCUMENT because the yellow ink is now gone Keep in mind the yellow ink had a little less than a of its ink remaining before I replaced the Black ink cartridge Now after replacing the Cyan cartridge now the yellow ink gone so I again replace it with a used cartridge that had about remaining but after this initializing process now all color ink cartridges are completely empty Keep in mind during this time I havent been able to PRINT a single document since replacing the Black cartridge the previous day So now I am completely out of three ink cartridges all because I changed out three cartridgesSo now I am so frustrated I want to throw the printer out my story office window if only the window opened In a last ditch effort I call HP Support to ask how I can bypass the color cartridges to print my black and white document I am told by support that the printer cannot print without the color cartridges When I ask why I am told that it is due to the printers high quality printing So when I ask how in Gods name does a yellow ink cartridge impact the quality of a black and white document I get crickets chirping from the support person until he asks if I would like to speak with a supervisor When I say yes he places me on hold until the system hangs up on me minutes later I call back now I immediately ask for a supervisor The supervisor tells me that is the way the printer is designed It uses color ink even in black and white documents to ensure quality printing and says he will send me a link to contact the CEO with my commentsMoral of the story NEVER buy a printer that requires color cartridges to print black and white documents There is only one reason that color ink is required to print black and white and it is to sell more ink cartridges This printer is purposefully wasting color inks in order to force the buyer to replace thecartridges as much as possible Until HP rewrites their printer software to eliminate this wasteful ink usage I think anyone that purchases any of their inkjet printers should have their head examined By the way I worked for HP in their Enterprise Software division so I am not just some HP hater

I have not used this exact model but we have four different earlier models with the same basic design as this printer The good prints well enough for office copies have not tried high quality photo printing rarely if ever jams on us fast draft copies scanner works well enough An incredible value and feature set for the money Also good is that the print head is not built into the ink tanks so you can get cheap ink replacements Surprisingly the ADF is reliable and doesnt jam when feeding multiple sheets as long as the pages arent dogeared The ones that we printscan with frequently every day have been real reliable workhorses The bad if you dont print often like going a week or two without printing eventually one of the print heads will clog This is pretty much true of almost any inkjet printer and the Brothers are no different Inkjet printers need to be used All inkjet printers including the Brother have head cleaning commands to fix this However at some point you will find that this is not enough and you simply cannot get the printer to print one or more colors When this happens your only hope is to clean the printheads manually The problem with the Brother printers of this design is that the print heads are buried inside the printer and are completely inaccessible Also it is impossible to disassemble the printer to access the print heads to clean them At some point if youre not consistently printing fairly often you may find that this product is hopelessly clogged and unusable as a printer as we have on two that we use infrequently For infrequent printing I would recommend looking at a plain inkjet printer that gives you easy access to the print heads Then again for this price if you only get a couple of years out of it its not all that bad

My office uses Sage Timeslips and has used it since Our current version is Timeslips We are an accounting firm and we bill for our time based on the amount of time spent on a project Timeslips is fine for this process Time accumulation billing and collections work fine After billing or collection a journal entry can be printed to post to your accounting program We use QuickBooks and are happy with this process Sage does not attempt to stay current with QuickBooks releases so the journal entries cannot be posted automaticallyI have rated the program a for functionality I am writing this review to discuss my most recent experience with technical support Timeslips quit working just after we had completed a month end billing run which does take some time I called customer support and explained that I was receiving a database error and did not want to restore the last backup because I would have to redo all of the billing which would take many hours First I must pay for technical support I paid and spent a half hour with the support person from India controlling my machine who then told me they were closing It was pm PST He copied the diagnostic from my computer and said I needed a database expert and they were also closed but call tomorrow morning The next morning I called and talked to a database expert who controlled my machine and said that I had a database error and he could not fix it I could send my database to Sage but they will probably charge me an additional charge for this and I should just restore my most current backup if I didnt want to do thisI am out about hours of my time plus approximately hours to redo my month end client billing since Sage could not fix my problem On each call I told them I had a database error and I didnt want to restore my last backup I would not waste your time and money attempting to get help from Sage technical support

Prior to getting a smartphone I loved keeping a planner This planner seemed perfect for getting back into the habit since it is small enough to tuck into my purse or carry with the rest of my belongings to a meeting Unfortunately this planner is laid out in such a way that makes it less practical to use There is a lot of dead empty space in the middle of the planner where the two pages meet I realize that writing in this area can be challenging but it means that the space for each day of the month is pretty small There is really only room to write a couple of items per day at most and that is with tiny writing Each month also has a note section on the side of the page This would be handy but again there is a minuscule amount of space really only enough room for one maybe two words on each line which doesnt make it tremendously easy to read or useOn the plus side the pattern is really pretty and I like that it was not just on the cover but on the pages as well The plastic sleeve is also a nice touch to keep the cover pristine Overall I think this could be an okay planner if you dont have much to keep track of or are only using it to reference a calendar but if you have a lot to write out this probably isnt the planner for you

June Update If amazon allowed me to change the number of stars I originally rated this item would change my original one star rating to stars I was pleased that Dixon the manufacturer showed Goodwill and sent me replacement boxes of pencils I would have given them stars but I still have problems with breaking lead I have found that the Dixon branded pencils by the same manufacturer have held up much better December Update I originally reviewed this product in April See my original review in the paragraph below It was based upon two separate purchases I made of the Dixon Ticonderoga box of a dozen pencils I had found that the lead was breaking constantly and or falling out Sharpening the pencils did not help The response that I got from a couple of other reviewers was that they couldnt disagree more with my review and that these were the best pencils they had ever owned One sarcastic reviewer commented that I should write a letter to the manufacturer Today I finally did contact the manufacturer and found out that yes indeed they did have a defect in the manufacturing of their pencils The defect has caused the pencil lead to break fall out and also to not sharpen properly They are supposed to send me replacement pencils I will update this review once I have received them and tried them April Review Ive never owned pencils that break as often as these do Im burning through a box of so quickly it is crazy It appears that they werent glued together very well during manufacture so they dont hold the lead evenly when they are sharpened Consequently the lead breaks very often Apparently Im not the only one that has experienced this with Ticonderoga Pencils Refer to the review of DIX Ticonderoga PencilsASINBUXOA DIX Ticonderoga Pencils

I bought this harness for my Mazda so I could hookup an aftermarket amp I wasnt replacing the head unit and I did not want to splice into the factiry harness So I bought both the regular harness MAB and the reverse harness MARB from Scosche thinking I could avoid cutting into my factory wire harness But this harness is missing several wires It does not have the illumination wires the steering wheel control wires or the wires used for the LED display that shows the clock and other functions In total it looks like wires are missing from the harness So if you use this harness you can no longer set the time on the clock see what radio station is tuned in see the volume level or control the head unit from the steering wheel controls I called Scosche and they suggested I buy six more harnesses and steal the wires from them to make one complete harness What a joke In my opinion the only reason to by the MAB harness is if you are replacing the head unit in which case you will lose the functionality of the LED screen and steering controls anyway I cant really see any reason to buy the reverse harness from Scosche since this implies that you are keeping the factory head unit and therefore want to retain the LED screen and steering wheel functionality In summary the only way I could get my amp wired was to splice into my factory harness These Scosche harness are worthless to me and Ill be sending them back

I bought this PDA after extensive obsessing over web reviews product information specs and visiting the red shirted and blue shirted sales associates at my local tech retail stores I chose the Casio BE for its functional ability and to supplement not replace my laptop I highly recommend this unit for those of you who like me need a small inexpensive yet fully functional color display PDA to record your calendar events take quick notes maintain Outlooklike contact lists and check basic email This unit does all this beautifully and synchronizes well with Outlook The only strange synchronization Ive found is that items sent from the PDA to Outlook are sometimes misspelled but never in the other direction I wonder if this is more due to my typing using the stylus and the smaller display rather than an actual synch problem The entire synch process is very easy to set up and operates seamlessly for calendar appointments todo tasks contact lists etcAs for the lack of software I dont use a PDA to play games use Word and manage spreadsheets for those I rely on real computers with at least a display great graphics card lots of RAM and cache a real joystick mouse and keyboard and a true sound system I just cant do this cramped by a screen smaller than a floppy disk I know how frustrating this can be because in my real computer was an OsborneI with a screen So trust me on this work in an ergonomic environment and if you seek diversion on those long flights buy an inexpensive hand held game and use this PDA for your true business needsIf youve used Pocket PCs in the past you will likely be thrown a bit by the menu system it reminds me of the old DOS shells such as dirplus that dont give you a functional desktop but require you to work through set menu levelIts thin the audience wont even notice you are having something at your hand for your hand can cover it well naturally Its easy to hold and allows me to keep my gestures during the presentation The texture is skinlike so you dont need much force to grab itThe timer is another highlight over other models A precise timing is allowed and you always have the idea on the flow especially useful when you are playing as a team For example I set minutes for my part when there were minutes left it vibrated to remind me finally vibrated again when the time is upThe buttons are well designed for through that hole actually I can see the PCBscomponentsthe electronic stuff inside the remoteWhen you are using it you may have to avoid dropping something through this hole into the remote or it Having never owned a pico projector before I was intrigued by the idea of them My old projector has a blown bulb and instead of spending another for a new bulb I decided I would give this a whirl I spend a lot of time at work or traveling so I wanted something to have handy if I ever wanted to play a game or watch a video on the go I just received my pk today and here are my initial impressionsPros Very small Lightweight Still feels durable despite and Bright picturethis one shocked me In my living room with the lights on granted this took place at night I could clearly see the picture when projected onto a wall across the room I imagine the result with my projector screen will be better Built in card reader and decoder work well I loaded some avis onto a memory card to test out how this would work Not only did it work quickly it also was able to find the avis I nested within a folder Built in speaker works surprisingly well Seems like optoma listened to some of the feedback from earlier models and included a remote and some accessories with this model Padded case seems niceCons There is no keystone adjustment feature This is actually a large issue in part because of the size of this unit If you put this on a tabledeskfurnitureetc theres a high chance you will not be directly centered from where you are projecting the image The tilt updownto the side causes very visible distortion in the image shape Its still watchable but this seems like a huge oversight for a projector that cost Fan is loud when on bright mode lumens Fan noise is most definitely audible when the projector is running at lumens This isnt a deal breaker and honestly its not terribly loud Even though the padded case seems nice there is no spot to put your charger or any accessories Unit heats upquickly I havent had it on for prolonged periods yet so Im not sure how this will effect the picture quality or processing I can tell you that during my minute trial runs today it became warm to the touch These were all during lumen bright mode tests so perhaps the effect is not as great on the normal mode Cords for accessories are short and move the projector if you are adjusting the input device position To fix this and help fix problem I would recommend getting a good minitripod I wouldnt skimp on something in the range I personally went with ASINBEVSLRO Joby GPAEN Gorillapod Flexible Tripod Grey and Black It was still relatively cheap and does an excellent job holding the projector firmly in position I imagine that tripod will also come in handy when I want to bring the projector outdoors along with some external speakers to have a movie night with friends No lens cap for the projector The lens appears to be made of plastic and is recessed but this still seems like an area for concern A small modification to add a lens cap which I cant imagine would cost much could have corrected this issueIll try to do a more detailed review soon and maybe a video review if I get enough time Overall I am pleased with the projector but I still have some other tests I want to do before rendering a final verdict If you go into this purchase expecting to get high definition movie theater quality imagesyou will be disappointed If you go into this realizing you are trading off movie theater quality picture and a huge projector in exchange for ease of portability while still maintaining a good picture you will likely be happyInitially Id give this a Update After having some time to play around with this I have some additional comments The sound is not nearly as loud as I thought when you are in a large room It is still better than nothing but you will likely need an external speaker of some sort to fully enjoy this Not a deal breaker though this is a small projector so this shouldnt come as a shock The unit is not as bright when played for a long time This was expected as Optoma has admitted their projector dims itself slightly if it gets too hot Mainly mentioning this so others are aware this is normal behavior I have had some severe problems when playing media directly off the projector either via micro SD or internal memory In a handful of cases the audio is out of sync In one case the audio did not play at all Other times when moving from one video file to another the projector simply will not play the file If I restart the projector the file plays fine These examples are all using files that meet the Optoma specifications for what the projector can play back I thought that there may be a chance the firmware was outdated but when I went to the Optoma site I couldnt even find firmware for this model Seems to be a big oversight I plan to call tech support tomorrow to find out what is going on Im going to do further testing on this issue but yesterday I started up my projector and after the Optoma logo I got a blank white screen It did not take me to the menu This continued several times until I plugged the projector into the charger Im not sure if this is normal behavior for when the unit is low on battery or if there is a bigger issue This is another item I plan to address with tech support tomorrowOverall I am still happy with this unit but a lot will be riding on my interaction with Optoma tech support tomorrow Ill keep this updated with the results Also I did get a chance to take some pictures in full fluorescent lighting as well as dim lighting Ill post those in a future updateUpdate I contacted Optoma tech support and they confirmed that myunit is faulty They said it either has bad software or a bad battery Strangely they advised me to return the unit to Amazon and have Amazon fulfill a new unit Strange specifically because the paper inside the box says STOP Call tech support and send your unit in for repair before returning it to your place of purchaseAt any rate I have my new unit now and Ill be testing it out during the week

I have purchased several of these Handspring GPS springboards and the Geoid though twice the price has the least functionality of any of them First the compass requires that you calibrate each time you are in a different environment This requires that you go through a compass set up process that includes holding the unit level and spinning slowly around in a circle This quickly grows annoying as you have to set it whenever you use the unit I tried calibrating in my car and the unit never would calibrate Whether intended or not most people will be buying this unit for use in the car Since it was unable to be calibrated in the car the icon showing the direction of travel never did work accurately The identity of streets are a mystery until you actually select them with your stylus Again when trying to drive to a location this is akward You either have to pull your car over everytime you need a street name or you pull this manuever off while driving Nearly impossible in a shaky car To navigate to a point their is no ability to indicate where the point is in reference to your current location So your only option is to zoom out to the extent that you can see both your location and the target location This makes it increasingly difficult to select a certain road and identify which one to take to your targetIn conclusion there are better springboards available for half the price Dont waste your money

I bought this printer when my old HP allinone finally died after six years and wouldnt pick up paper any longer Im giving the printer two stars because the color output does look nice for regular pages Ive not tried printing any photos on it so I cant really comment on thatNow for the negatives I spend a huge amount of time clearing nonexistent paper jams from this printer Basically anytime the printer doesnt want to pick up the paper which is often it decides it has a paper jam Clearing a paper jam requires removing the back cover This means that the printer really cant be conveniently located against a wall unless you want to keep pulling it out and turning it around Repeatedly taking off the back cover and reinstalling it seems for me at least to inevitably lead to slightly misaligning the print head When the printer sees this condition it requires a recalibration Other printers Ive owned have made recalibration optional but for this printer it seems to be mandatory You cant use it again until it prints the calibration page The calibration page uses lots of ink Speaking of ink usage the printer seems to use more ink than other printers Ive owned So even though the ink may cost a tiny bit less than other brands youll go through more of it The printer also requires both color and BW cartridges with ink in them in order to print Other printers typically allow you to print with one if the other is dry as long as the empty cartridge is still in the slot So even if you plan to print only BW youll end up using the more expensive color cartridge anyway I had to uninstall the antivirussecurity program CA Security Center on my laptop in order to use the wireless feature with this printer I finally found that Microsoft Security Essentials does work okay with the printer I tried to find some way to get both to work at the same time but it was impossible Im not technologically challengedIm the ops manager for a supercomputing center The wireless component of the printer software is just very cumbersome and difficult to work withIn sum I wish I hadnt been taken in by the claims of cheaper printing made on the packaging This printer has been a headache Once I feel like I have gotten my moneys worth out of it then Ill give it away and go buy a new HP The old HP wasnt perfect but it printed on the first try every time never jammed allowed for BWonly printingcopying and seemed to have a less intrusive software interfaceEditing My Review Ive changed my review from two stars to one star Now when the printer does pick up paper which is still seldom it doesnt actually print anything on the page It feeds the page through and makes all of the noises one would expect when a page is printing but the output is blank All of the components are installed correctly and the ink cartridges are at least half full so there is no obvious reason for this to happen I suppose I could try to go through all of the troubleshooting procedures and looking up codes on the Kodak Web site etc but Ive wasted enough time and frustration already

Averys White Repositionable Address Labels arrived in a welldesigned professionally wrapped packageSix labels using three label sheets were produced on a laser HP printer The labels designation is but wellpositioned instructions were placed right below that number telling the user to use Averys template to run the labelsThe box advises guaranteed smudge free and jam free and in both cases they were Avery advertises their Popup Edge for fast peeling and that feature also worked as advertisedFor this test we sent selfaddressed white envelopes using Sparco brand Regular Business Envelopes model manufactured by SP Richards Company of Atlanta GA This information is included as Avery advised on the box that results may vary based on paper characteristics that the product could be attached toThe envelopes were address to our home but also two PO boxes that are not at the same location This would guarantee different handlings as the labels traveled through the postal systemThe labels were attached to the envelopes and all three were removed and repositioned Five minutes later they were pulled up and repositioned again all with no difficulty Then they were placed on a car seat loose in a heated garage whose temperature was about degrees After an overnight stay all three were inspected and all three had lifted off the envelope about a quarter inch on the right side of the label They were pushed down on the envelopes and they stayed down all three were placed under a heavy bookThree hours later they were inspected again and all three were fully attached They were then mailed at a post office unrelated to either post office destination and we waited for deliveryThe next day all three arrived at their destinations All three were firmly attached to their envelopes With considerable effort we were able to peel back one corner on one label but under all reasonable circumstances the labels had firmly attached to the envelope just as advertisedWe now have a problem The instructions advised that results may vary based on paper characteristics All three labels lifted after an overnight stay in a car but in fairness all three were attached to envelopes made by the same vendor so we pressed on Two extra return envelopes from various vendors were labeled and also a label was affixed to the letter from Avery that described the product All three were placed loose on the car seat just as the first three wereThe next morning all three showed very minor lifting on the right side of the label Not much but they could be peeled off easily All three were pressed down and they stayed down No weight was placed on them and three hours later they had fully adhered to the document and the two envelopes and could have been mailedConclusion These labels do many of the things they advertise right out of the box and do of what they advertise but as you saw time and effort was required I would not feel confident in mailing an important document using these labels Sadly I just dont think they are quite ready for prime timeRossionable circumstances the labels had firmly attached to the envelope just as advertised We now have a problem The instructions advised that First off Amazon had the cheapest price on this printer ANYWHERE It looks out of stock now but if it came back in stock this is the place to get it I bought this for my husband for Christmas He actually needed a new scanner as his was old but our generic printer could have been updated too And I liked that it had the copy feature The prints are quick and quite good We havent tried printing anything major or any photos yet but so far no problems with the printing He had a slight issue with the scanner at first It took FOREVER to scan because it actually has to configure itself before every single scan But even we were suspicious at the amount of time it took So he called tech support and they told him that one of his Mac drivers were out of date So he downloaded new ones and problem solved It still has to configure itself every time you scanunless you keep scan on the whole time but its nowhere near as slow After the scan actually gets goin its very quick And honestly I think the constant configuration is for people that have a Mac or at least that is what the tech guy told him We havent tried the slide scanning feature yet or the copier But for this price range it has everything you are looking for and I think its a great deal Also my husband is a graphic designer so he needs his scans to be crisp looking and I know hes satisfied so it was worth it just for that One minor issue is the size of the printer It is pretty large but if you have a decent amount of room on your table we have Lshaped desks then its not really a big deal The LCD screen is a neat feature as well

Ok this is the review you want to read for historical use of the printerSo when I initially bought this printer it was great Brand spanking new with that new printerelectronic smell Setup was a breeze The install went without a single issue on WiFi and USB Faxing Copying Printing all worked fine and the prints were fabulous So stars for printing a photo or a couple pages of something This was my thought upon unboxing it and using it the first couple of daysThus the downfall beginsAbout month later I had to replace both the Black and Color cartridges I had only printed maybe sheets up to this point I figured it was because they were starter cartridges and didnt think anything of it because I was told Kodaks Ink per Dollar value was the best on the market So I went to my local Staples bought the cheaper than the competition cartridges installed them and was back in business And just to be clear I mean actual name brand Kodak cartridges and not some knockoff brand I only use the phrase cheaper than the competition to make a point and you will see more as you read thisAbout months later I got the Ink is low messages for the cartridges Their levels were a little different so it wasnt like the software keeping track was faulty thinking both were low but really I think Id only printed about pages this time and mostly BW text so I started scratching my head as to why the color would be so low I wasnt even breaking the pages mark So I checked online for some tips and realized that I was always printing the highest quality prints even if it was just a quick BW text page So I adjusted the resolution down to half went back to Staples once again bought the cheaper than the competition cartridges installed them and was back in businessAnother months later Ink is low So adjusting the print quality extended me more month I think this time I made it to about or pages Again mostly BW text yet both Black and Color were low OK at this point I knew something was up I check the printer for leaks checked the Printer Heads ran the calibrations everything checked out fine I also found that when the Black gets low the Color cartridges starts to fill in to create black This would explain why they were both showing low Even though I was mainly printing BW text the black was obviously draining so quickly that the color took over and drained quickly as well But again just months and less than pagesSo I started consulting reviews and quickly found that although a lot of people like myself felt this was an awesome to star printer that feeling quickly faded to a star It doesnt matter if your to purchase of ink is cheaper than the competition if you are constantly having to buy cartridges for basic printing every monthsSo I have decided to replace it with a laser printer that can print pages off of toner cartridge and has the history to back it up Even with the knowledge that the cost of a laser toner cartridge is higher when compared side by side to an inkjet cartridge not having to replace ink so frequently is well worth the price and aggravation At most this Kodak printer is nothing more to me than a FAX machine and flatbed scanner at this point

I purchased this stand to hold my monitors x x and x for an UpLift sitstand desk I chose this stand because the pole was taller than most so I could some additional height as I wanted to mount the bottom left and right monitors in portrait mode I also liked the base because it was flat and looked less obtrusive than most of the other stands This is a great stand It is well made and very solid Its easily to assemble and the monitors are easy to adjust after they have been mounted The base does take up a lot of space on my desk more so than I was prepared for but it is pretty thin and flat so I barely even notice its there since I can easily put other things on top of it There are a few things I wish they would improve on the stand but I wont take any stars off as I think they are pretty specific as to how i want my monitors configured The curve isnt nearly as aggressive as I would like but I think Im in the minority for this given the angle I see most people use for multiple monitor setups I fixed my issues by buying standoffs and longer screws to mount the monitors on the included brackets so they extend out farther and the bezels can line up even with the more extreme angles Even with the standoffs the monitors feel very secure It would be nice if they would include some of those parts in the stand like they do for many TV mounting stands or offer an accessory kit I could buy to make it more adjustable right out of the box without me having to head to the hardware store I ended up not mounting my bottom left and right monitors on the stand and using the monitors stands instead because I am using them in page view If I had mounted them on the stand there would have been a huge gap between the topbottom rows for the center monitors It would be nice if they offered some type of standoff bracket that could be used independently with the fixed center mount bracket to accommodate a portraitlandscapeportrait setup for the bottom row where the tops of all monitors lined up It looks like I could purchase an additional cross bar and mount that one on a lower set of holes to solve my problem Tyke doesnt have any parts listed on their site so I was unable to do so However I also didnt call the company to see if they would sell me one Im guessing they probably would have if I has called as they were very nice and helpful when I called them with some presales questions Overall I am very happy with the purchase of this stand and I would recommend it to anyone looking for a multimonitor stand

I received this book as a gift at a shower and had never seen anything like it My son was born prematurely and I became accustomed to his day being charted in the hospital NICU I was so used to knowing how many diapers he had or how much he ate during the day that I knew I would continue to keep track of this stuff when he first came home This book is a fabulous way to keep track of your babys day It has a spot for feedings activities medications diapers naps and then it has space to write in how he was in the morning and the evening It was a great way for me to know how much he ate and slept which made it easy for me to tell if he was having an off day and assisted me in better meeting his needs When I went to work I had my sons caregiver use it and it was a great way for me to review how his day was and helped me feel like I knew what was going on even though I was away
